You have extraneous annotations. it should be:


    @AfterClass
    public static void tearDownClass() throws Exception {
        // Code executed after the last test method 
    }

That method itself should be static in order to perform the teardown, and itself should *not* be a `@Test`.

**in Kotlin**
The structure of a test class would look like:

&lt;!-- language-all: kotlin --&gt;

    class MyTestClass {
        companion object {
            init {
               // things that may need to be setup before companion class member variables are instantiated
            }

            // variables you initialize for the class just once:
            val someClassVar = initializer() 

            // variables you initialize for the class later in the @BeforeClass method:
            lateinit var someClassLateVar: SomeResource 
      
            @BeforeClass @JvmStatic fun setup() {
               // things to execute once and keep around for the class
            }

            @AfterClass @JvmStatic fun teardown() {
               // clean up after this class, leave nothing dirty behind
            }
        }

        // variables you initialize per instance of the test class:
        val someInstanceVar = initializer() 

        // variables you initialize per test case later in your @Before methods:
        var lateinit someInstanceLateZVar: MyType 

        @Before fun prepareTest() { 
            // things to do before each test
        }

        @After fun cleanupTest() {
            // things to do after each test
        }

        @Test fun testSomething() {
            // an actual test case
        }

        @Test fun testSomethingElse() {
            // another test case
        }

        // ...more test cases
    }  

Given the above, you should read about:

* [companion objects](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/classes.html#companion-objects) - similar to the Class object in Java, but a singleton per class that is not static
* [`@JvmStatic`](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/java-to-kotlin-interop.html#static-methods) - an annotation that turns a companion object method into a static method on the outer class for Java interop
* [`lateinit`](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/properties.html#late-initialized-properties) - allows a `var` property to be initialized later when you have a well defined lifecycle
* [`Delegates.notNull()`](https://kotlinlang.org/api/latest/jvm/stdlib/kotlin.properties/-delegates/not-null.html) - can be used instead of `lateinit` for a property that should be set at least once before being read.

